html: _Cimilikā_. Sp.2.112(VRI): _Cimilikā nāma sudhādiparikammakatāya bhūmiyā vaṇṇānurakkhaṇatthaṁ katā hoti, taṁ heṭṭhā pattharitvā upari kaṭasārakaṁ pattharanti_—“A _cimilikā_ is made to protect the color of a floor that has been plastered, etc. It is spread out underneath, with a straw-mat spread out on top.” {}
<dd>_Akappiyakataṁ hoti_, literally, “It is done with what is not allowable.” The “it,” both here and below, refers to the ceremony of making it allowable, and the “what” refers to the food. {}
